Step 1: Calculate Gross Profit Margin.
• From the income statement, Gross Profit = 2,741,764.34 and Total Revenue = 5,991,764.34.
• Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100 = (2,741,764.34 / 5,991,764.34) × 100 ≈ 45.73%

Step 2: Calculate Operating Cash Flow Ratio.
• From the cash flow statement, Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = 215,423.24.
• From the balance sheet, Total Current Liabilities = 1,124,588.25.
• Operating Cash Flow Ratio = (Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities / Total Current Liabilities) = 215,423.24 / 1,124,588.25 ≈ 0.19

Thus, the answer is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Gross Profit Margin": "45.73%",
    "Operating Cash Flow Ratio": "0.19"
  }
}
